data.title: Entertainment (General)
data.meta_description: Woody Allen - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Woody Allen is an American film director, writer, actor, and comedian whose career spans over 50 years. He began as a comedy writer in the 1950s and developed a neurotic, intellectual persona as a stand-up comedian. Allen wrote and directed over 50 films, often starring himself. Some of his most acclaimed films include Annie Hall (1977), Manhattan (1979), and Hannah and Her Sisters (1986). He has won four Academy Awards and is one of the most influential filmmakers of the New Hollywood era.
